From: https://forums.factorio.com/viewtopic.php?p=146142#p146142

- the topmost tile row MUST NOT contain any pipes that could be able to connect to the north, which would then be the lowest tile row of the rack above this one.
- belts and pipes MAY be omitted if all racks above or below don't need either. When omitting it MUST be possible to rebuild the belts and pipes from the original blueprint.
-Due to the symmetry of the layout, two belts and one pipe are unused.

blueprint_book.label: Modular Extensible PnP Factory V3.1
blueprint_book.description:
From: https://forums.factorio.com/viewtopic.php?p=146142#p146142
Concept by: dee- - https://forums.factorio.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&u=5697
Currently Version 3.1 is the current version of the bus and rack layout for the Modular Extensible PnP Factory System.

 -  A rack MUST always be 13 fields high. It is never shorter and never longer.
-   A standardized belt and pipe system exists. Its connectors to the north and to the south MUST be preserved.
